title: For Sale:  Astra 600 9mm
postcontent: Up for sale is an Astra 600 9mm. This is a cool historic pistol. The gun was made in Spain for Germany during World War 2, and about 60,000 pistols were made, although only the first 10,500 were delivered before the liberation of France cut off the supply lines between Spain and Germany. The remaining pistols were primarily sold after the war to West Germany for police use, with a smaller number being purchased by the Portugese Navy. This pistol is however missing some safety components (safety catch detent, detent spring, safety catch, mag safety spring, and mag safety). Parts numbers 16,17,38,40,41 on Numrich. Armslist turns my photos upside down for some reason but if your interested just contact me and i can send any pictures you want.

postcontent:
Everyone is always offering trades. I have plenty of rifles already. Up for grabs is a deer rifle that I put a big scope on and never sighted it in.
 
About 20 years ago it seems, my father bought this rifle new for me from Van’s.
 
Synthetic stock. Shorter barrel. I may have hunted with it 3 times open sights. Killed one deer.
 
In this for sell deal, is the slightly expensive big scope that I added, but didn’t sight in and all the ammo that I have for it.
 
No trades.
 
Take it or leave it.
 
In the 1960s, my dad won a Winchester 100 .284 rifle. The rifle will be up for sale soon. It is a collector’s item.  It was his favorite gun. He has taken many deer with it. All that to say, I had planned to just to sale the barrel off this rifle (or buy another 700) and put on a custom .284 barrel to keep the .284 caliber alive, but my kids aren’t interested in maintaining my dad’s love of the .284 and now I am playing with building ar-15 / ar-10, so I am going to list this gun.
 
If you don’t have the money, I understand.
 
Shipping? No I don’t want your “totally legitimate  cashier’s check”.  If you are really all that interested in me shipping the rifle to your FFL, there will be a 3 week hold waiting for your payment to clear plus $50 shipping charges.
